rComments: Do you want to be a grad student? This is the best practice you'll get in undergrad. It's a hard course but he reveals some of the most important and pertinent issues in clinical psychology/psychiatry. He's very open to well researched and "creative" views, and will always reward you accordingly.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Great lecturer. I took his seminar course and it completely reinvented my perspective on clinical psychology. His lecturing style is very engaging, and although you have to write 5 papers (worth 20% each) for his class, there are no exams and no huge "final paper". His course really prepares you for graduate school (if you're interested in that).
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Best professor at UTSC. He makes you look at topics in ways you hadn't been challenged to do before. He is picky about writing but it helps you improve and he gives you great feedback. He has inspired me to look at psychology differently and more passionately. Highly recommend taking CT in abnormal psych with him, you won't regret it!
